				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Rizlona's Fire<a name="15457"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 13 04 4:40 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Basically, the deal with the upcoming wizard familiar with a DD focus component, as I understand it:
<br />

<br />
A person's final focus % is the sum of one spell/song effect (such as Call of the Muse) and one item effect (such as IDIV or better).  This is the reason why our focus songs stack with focus effect items in the first place.
<br />

<br />
The highest percentage in each category is the one that is used in the calculations.  This is similar to haste percentages in that respect.
<br />

<br />
So, the wizard familiar would take precedence over our current songs (assuming the final percentage for the familiar's DD focusing is set at 30%).  This would simply mean the wizard's nuke damage would go up, regardless of whether or not he was grouped with a bard.  However, his other benefits from the non-focusing familiars would be lost.  It's a trade-off, and whether or not a bard is in the group might help him to decide which familiar to use.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Melees love us for the haste; casters love us for the mana; fleeing loonies love us for the Selo's.<br>
---Bard Motto<br>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=910907>Lenowill's Magelo profile</a></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
